title: `codegen/stack-probes.rs` fails on AArch64
body:
The `codegen/stack-probes.rs` test fails on AArch64 with the following output:

```
---- [codegen] codegen/stack-probes.rs stdout ----
        
error: verification with 'FileCheck' failed
status: exit code: 1
command: /home/mmatyas/rustc-nightly/build/build/aarch64-unknown-linux-gnu/llvm/build/bin/FileCheck -input-file=/home/mmatyas/rustc-nightly/build/build/aarch64-unknown-linux-gnu/test/codegen/stack-probes.ll /home/mmatyas/rustc-nightly/rust/src/test/codegen/stack-probes.rs
stdout:
------------------------------------------

------------------------------------------
stderr:
------------------------------------------
/home/mmatyas/rustc-nightly/rust/src/test/codegen/stack-probes.rs:24:11: error: expected string not found in input
// CHECK: attributes #0 = { {{.*}}"probe-stack"="__rust_probestack"{{.*}} }
          ^
/home/mmatyas/rustc-nightly/build/build/aarch64-unknown-linux-gnu/test/codegen/stack-probes.ll:7:36: note: scanning from here
define void @foo() unnamed_addr #0 {
                                   ^
/home/mmatyas/rustc-nightly/build/build/aarch64-unknown-linux-gnu/test/codegen/stack-probes.ll:12:1: note: possible intended match here
attributes #0 = { uwtable }
^

------------------------------------------

thread '[codegen] codegen/stack-probes.rs' panicked at 'explicit panic', /home/mmatyas/rustc-nightly/rust/src/tools/compiletest/src/runtest.rs:2479:8
note: Run with `RUST_BACKTRACE=1` for a backtrace.


failures:
    [codegen] codegen/stack-probes.rs

test result: FAILED. 35 passed; 1 failed; 9 ignored; 0 measured; 0 filtered out
```

I've tried cross compiling with remote testing on an Acer Chromebook R13, and also building and testing natively on a Juno development board.
